I've been working on this EP for the past two years, and only recently was I able to finish it (collaborations make projects more difficult to finish, who would have thought :)). But yeah, join me on this journey and support in any way you can. Sharing it with a friend is already enough!!

title: BUZZ - Liberation [Sound of Fractures Remix]
description:
I discovered this song in January when it came out, and had been using as a part of my DJ set, so when I saw it was on sound and that the stems were available it felt like the stars were aligning. The remix is imperfect, its chaotic and its not an arrangement a label would ever approve, so it made me feel excited about making music again. 

This drop represents what I love about this platform, its a place I can release music that I never felt I could before. It will only exist here, and I love that. 

I made this at a time where I really needed an emotional release, and after getting a spot in the Optimism We Love Art competition for my project SCENES my head was spinning, but creating music grounds me.. and so does releasing it into the world on my own terms. 

If you like this remix then check out my SCENES project now, and take part by submitting a memory!

Much love and thanks for your support.

J xx

title: Liberation
description:
BUZZ was spiraling and took a drive to the mountains -  daunted by fear of her dreams never coming true. She pulled off the side of the road in a fit of rage and wrote a poem which I will spare you from but ended like:

To do it with everything in my soul even if for an empty auditorium
A barren stadium
A silent theater
A grave yard
A dark encompassing void
To reveal every corner of my humanity to a world full of distracted bodies who might never turn an ear...
And still do it with the loudest expression 

She drove home feeling cleansed and wrote Liberation in a matter of minutes.

title: Halo Dreamer
description:
A step inside the Raver Realm universe.

The collectible linking @soundxyz_ to the Music PFP collection Raver Realm by Jadyn Violet.

Halo Dreamer is a song written and produced by Jadyn Violet.

Collect 5 limited edition Dreamers -> Get airdropped 1 random Raver from the major collection Raver Realm.

Raver Realm is important because it redefines what a music collectible is. This premium 1800 collection consists of 9 original songs that are personified into Raver characters. 

All characters in the Raver universe were hand drawn by Jadyn Violet and are dynamic. 

This means as the songs (also known as Ravers) go up in streams on Spotify -> The Ravers levels up unlocking various utilities. 

Bringing music to life like never before!

Halo Dreamer is the first of many "Lost Ravers." Lost Ravers are not part of the original 9 Raver characters from Raver Realm. Halo Dreamer is a track that encapsulates the nostalgia of loving someone so deeply. The act of something as simple as smelling an old lovers perfume becomes a catalyst to rehash all of the old feelings of lust. "She took out my old perfume and started geeking." 

Jadyn has a belief that fans can relate to music so much more than they are right now. Taking a song and turning it into a character lets someone relate to the story a lot more than simply listening to lyrics and productions. That is what Jadyn did with Raver Realm, and what he hopes to continue pushing with the Lost Raver "Halo Dreamer."

title: DRIVE ME MAD.
description:
This song was created over the internet - just like our friendship. 

When me and Reo first started to work together we were in two different cities: I would fly from LA to Vegas to write and he would crash on my couch in LA if we weren‚Äôt out there. That process went on for months at a time.

Eventually I coerced him and his wife to move back to LA and ironically we have worked together in person less than we ever did when we were in two different cities.

Reo and I are both interesting types of introverts - in a way that similarity has probably been what‚Äôs kept us such close friends and collaborators over the years. While we‚Äôre down to be the life of the party from time to time, we individually spend the vast majority of our lives working out of our bedroom studios.

Our lives have changed so much since releasing music onchain. DRIVE ME MAD. is a look into that reflection.

title: I Just Need (Stripped)
description:
"I Just Need" is my most popular song, and it's changing my life in real time.

Daniel and I released our version of this song in August and we've both never seen a reaction like this before ‚Äî people are singing the words at shows, I've received messages from people who have told me this song gets them through their day, and it's growing faster than anything I've ever been a part of before.

I wrote this song at a vulnerable time in my life and it's been incredibly moving to see it now live as the soundtrack for so many other people.

I wanted to release a stripped back version to highlight the more emotional undertone of it, and bring it closer to the world that it first lived in when I wrote it.

‚Äî‚Äî

I'm submitting this song as part of the Optimism competition. 

Enjoy <3

description:
Citadel is the R≈åHKI theme song - first debuted on rohki.xyz

It‚Äôs been the cornerstone to our world and a moment we‚Äôve patiently waited to release until now.

A full, newly scored version of the track is being shared as our submission for Optimism‚Äôs onchain art competition - and as a tribute to the end of Season 1 and an ode to Season 2.

description:
‚ÄúRelief (Solo),‚Äù off Heno.‚Äôs upcoming album "I'm Tired Of Being Hypersurveilled," marks a turning point in the poignant narrative of the artist, producer, and innovator‚Äôs larger concept project. Accompanied by the RELIEF pixel game where arcade tickets minted on ZORA unlock power ups, ‚ÄúRelief (Solo)‚Äù soundtracks Heno.‚Äôs character‚Äôs pursuit of an escape. ‚ÄúDealing with a topic like surveillance, there's a lot of nuance, and a lot of ways to go‚Äìdifferent topics or subtopics to speak on. But I knew escape, relief or pursuit of being free was a sentiment that needed to be on an album like this,‚Äù says Heno. 

Speaking to Heno.‚Äôs personal experience as a black man in America‚Äìthe project‚Äôs allegorical storyline was introduced by a three-part short film released last January in which Heno.‚Äôs character attends a PTSD Anonymous meeting that turns out to be a ploy for the S.Y.S.T.E.M. (Securing Your Safety Through Extreme Means) to spy on attendees. Eventually, his character is kidnapped (as depicted in the ‚ÄúNeybors‚Äù and ‚ÄúSIMMER DOWN‚Äù videos) before being thrown into a simulation seen in the interactive RELIEF pixel video game at which point Heno.‚Äôs character realizes he must find relief and escape. ‚ÄúThis is the point where I recognize I need to get out of the simulation one way or another, even if it means I have to burn the establishment down. I needed to get out. And I wanted to capture the frustration and the feeling of being gaslit while dealing with surveillance and people invalidating your experiences.‚Äù

Written, produced, and performed by Heno., ‚ÄúRelief‚Äù ‚Äìthe ninth track off HIGH FREQUENCY Volume 2‚Äìviscerally captures the feverish and exhausting feeling of being chased. ‚ÄúIt started with the production‚Äìplaying around with different synthesizers, and then I came across certain sounds that sounded like a chase. The beat sounds like I‚Äôm running from something, I'm literally trying to get the fuck out of there, and that urgency of being in pursuit.‚Äù 

Both futuristic and retro, the industrial nature of the track is perfect for the addictive video game, while simultaneously drawing attention to the very real experience that fueled its creation. ‚ÄúYou gotta make this shit make sense for you but for me, freedom from it all (as well as relief) is what I really want.

title: Annika Rose - Unforgettable
description:
As a writer and ever-evolving human being, most of my songs come from real experiences. Whether they be my own, or somebody else‚Äôs. Although they‚Äôre all widely open for interpretation, some are a little more transparent in the details. 

Unforgettable is one of those songs. 

As most women do, I have a deeply loving but equally as complicated relationship with my mom. I love her more than I‚Äôll ever love anyone, but she also knows how to twist the knife so effortlessly in ways nobody else does. And when a lot of those wounds continue to open back up time and time again, it‚Äôs difficult to not be reminded they‚Äôre there every day. 

When something is so prevalent and reoccurring, it tends to interrupt the peace I continue to try and culminate in my life. Sometimes my closest friend in moments of pain is my piano.

'Unforgettable' was born in a studio on Sunset Boulevard with a couple of my closest collaborators, Paul Phamous and Bailey Lindley. It was a slow burn to completion and took almost two years of going back in to refine the tiniest details til I was satisfied with it. It‚Äôs a testament to how powerful this song is, for me at least, because it resonates with the same intensity as it did when i first wrote it."

title: bololo
description:
Before you ask, the word 'bololo' is a slang term native to my hometown Barranquilla. we use it to describe a big mess, a brawl, something along those lines. but it can also mean a huge party that is just super out of control.

When I was working on this track initially with The Fund, Mark Johns, and Kate Morgan, they asked if there were any cool spanish words we could write around. I obviously hopped on google and looked up Coste√±o slang (coste√±o is what people from Barranquilla are called!) and bololo came up - as you can see we went with it!

I wanted the song to sound like what the word means - hence why the track is pretty crazy production-wise! I also decided to write about a crazy night, I just put myself in the shoes of someone who went out and had one of those nights where you end up in 6 different places, meet 3 people, become friends, and never see them again. I have personally never experienced anything like this so it was pretty fun to just dramatize what this whole ordeal would be like.

We all had the most fun making and recording this song, there are so many little details hidden in it that make it so special, you just have to listen to it over and over again I guess! enjoy "bololo"!!!

title: Time is Amazing
description:
Going Nowhere (Enjoying the Ride) was my first album.  

I've poured all my passion and my experiences as a young man into every note of those tracks. Recorded over 2 days in the spring of 2014, with some incredible Italian jazz musicians.  

Recording and releasing this album was a milestone moment in my artistic development. A journey that spanned continents, cultures, and emotions.

At that point in time I had graduated from the "G. Rossini Conservatory of Music" and traveled through most of Europe and Australia, meeting hundreds of incredible musicians, busking on the beautiful streets of Sydney, London, Paris, Rome, etc.
I also played each and every gig I could find, with all kinds of bands, musicians and DJs. Little by little expanding my musical horizons, acquiring knowledge, feeling and taste.  
  
My journey then took me to Berlin, where I refined my jazz chops.
I played hundreds of shows around the world with my quartet and supporting other amazing musicians.  

Then, in 2020, when live music went away, I took that as an opportunity to search for new avenues to release and monetize my music. I found an answer in blockchain technology.
With no limitations imposed by traditional standards, I let my creativity run wild.

I released my first album on Ethereum in March 2021, 'Nifty Sax Genesis', followed in September 2021 by 'Spheres', which was a ground-breaking success.  
  
My success inspired me to co-found Nifty Music, a music NFT incubator helping fellow artists create their own successful projects.
Nifty Music projects collectively generated over $1 million to-date for our independent artists and their communities.

And here we are now at the present moment, with yet another important milestone, the first music NFT I release to include music from my back catalog.

title: The Precipice
description:
I made The Precipice while getting acquainted with GrimesAI and going through a mini existential crisis throughout the wave of AI news earlier this year. I've always found technology creatively inspiring but its hard not to think about all the unforeseen risks, especially for frontier tech advancing at an exponential rate.

Given my concerns, I appreciate how Grimes has always embraced tech while not losing sight of what is special about being human. She is also an inspiration to me musically, so I was really excited to make a song using her voice.

The title of the song is borrowed from a book of the same name about existential risk (by Tony Ord). It made me think about how our relationship with AI is similar to falling in love: incredibly exciting and potentially life-changing, but could end like a Shakespearean tragedy if we aren't lucky or prepared. 

That metaphor inspired me to make a music video using the 1993 film adaptation of Romeo & Juliet, reimagined through an AI image generator:
https://youtu.be/_WssPKL1vIA

title: Lights on me ft. Caueiro (the crowdfunding track)
description:
üö®This song is part of a crowdfunding and every collector get very cool benefits, read the text bellow so you can get to know more about me and my project better üö® MUCH LOVE üíï
Hi there! Although some of you might know me as Yaxx, my real name is Yagna. That's what my mom calls me.

I'm a singer-songwriter from Havana, Cuba. I'm a mother to an amazing 5-year-old boy. My favorite color is purple, and I recently turned 27.
I wanted to be a doctor for a short time, but I honestly can't remember when I wasn't dreaming about performing my heart out on stage.
I started working with a band as a singer when I was only 18 years old and bought my first acoustic guitar on my 19th birthday by saving up my earnings. I've been writing songs for as long as I can remember. The first time I played my guitar, I wrote the song that changed my life, "Mercedes Benz." Yes, I tend to personalize things as abstract as a song because honesty is what unlocks the soul in my music. Working with a "cover" band has taught me a lot in the past seven years. I gained stage presence. Performing Led Zeppelin songs helped me improve my vocal abilities, but nothing compares to the feeling of standing on stage and singing the stories I've written.

In 2020 with the quarantine, all I had was my guitar, so I took that forced break from my routine to improve my songwriting. I helped two Cuban artists finish their albums (for legal reasons, I cannot share their names). I discovered some magical stuff about writing in Spanish (which I am now obsessed with).

I released my first song in Spanish on all digital platforms on September 18th, 2021, called "Deja Vu," since then, my life has been an incredible roller coaster.

I joined Twitter in January 2022 to help promote a collection, and little did I know, I was heading to the warmest place I'd been in forever.
My journey as a Web 3 artist started on the Tezos Blockchain, where I released three singles that were somehow related but weren't part of a collection. These songs were all acoustic performances recorded on my cellphone. My most successful song of those three was "Viernes," my first to sell out and which later became my first collaboration with my now producer and partner Caueiro. This collaboration became my debut on Catalog, a 1/1s music market on the Ethereum Blockchain, collected by Xcelencia. For that, I am eternally grateful.

I am a "me and my guitar" kind of performer when it comes to my music, but with the profit of my latest collection on objkt.com, "Yaxx's Nine Lives," I was able to switch things up and gather other musicians, I admired for a long time. This gave life to "Numerolog√≠a," my own little band, which we debuted during a concert on my 27th birthday. Needless to say, it was a dream come true!

I can proudly say I now have enough material to record and release my first full-length album: NUMEROLOGIA: THE ALBUM, a 9 tracks love story.
I'm super excited to share this album with the world.
Being a full-time singer in Cuba is a constant struggle financially. Life in Cuba can be challenging even for people that are not professional artists.

For context, selling one edition is listed at
0.005 eth (~9 USD) equals a two-month concert salary. I won't mention the daily living expenses because this is NOT about that. This is about music and art and love!

So, I am releasing a crowdfunding NFT. I've written a beautiful, soulful song called "Lights on Me," which encompasses everything I am attracting and manifesting for this new career era. This will be a limited edition, 540 editions (yes, I have a thing for the number nine, and I can tell the number nine has a thing for me as well). 

The Lights on Me NFT will be listed at 0.01 eth (approximately 20 USD at the time of this article) and is available from August 27th
Our main goal is to collect at least 540 editions before November 25th (90 days) to release the full album on April 27th.

Below are the details of the benefits of being a holder:
All the holders get access to Metaverse concerts and behind-the-scenes content of the album process and receive merch! This care package will include a personalized hand-written note expressing my gratitude and some fabulous album material.

The maximum amount of mints per wallet will be 5 editions. The more editions that are minted means more benefits to the holders:
1 minted= access to presale to the album with a 50% discount.
2 minted= access to presale to the album with a 75% discount.

4 minted= 1 free copy of the album AND  a custom NFT cover song
5 minted=  free copy of the album AND  a custom NFT cover song and a 25% discount on future mints, no matter the Blockchain.
Follow me on all social media platforms (@yaxx_castillo), and be sure to turn on notifications, as there will be many spaces and performances over the next 90 days. I'm always glad to connect and get to know my followers and supporters. Thanks for reading. Much love.

title: Under The Same Stars
description:
Under The Same Stars is a very special song to me. It has been almost 3 years since I left someone that meant the world to me. This track was born when I was looking up at the stars one night and had a sudden feeling. I felt for some reason she was out there looking up too. As if we were sharing the night sky that evening. 

Imagine that, in a world where two lovers are completely apart emotionally and physically, they still share the same stars. In a weird way, that idea is comforting <4

This is an exclusive free mint for only 50 lucky people.

The reason I am not selling this song, is because while I am still working everyday on my major music nft project called "Raver Realm," I wanted to give something special out to the community for free. The major project will be coming out very soon and I cannot wait for you guys to experience it.

Shout out to @gendotwav and @davesocozy for the additional production to the track :)

title: moneymorphosis (EP)
description:
"moneymorphosis" is a story about how money can positively change a person‚Äôs life, and then how that person can change their perspective on money.

i grew up with a single mother in inglewood, california. although we still had help from my father who lived the bronx, financial stability wasn‚Äôt familiar to us. we had love, closeness, and all the true necessities a human being needs. but since money was our biggest obstacle, it became the ultimate goal. i‚Äôm sure anyone who comes from struggle can resonate.

if i was wiser, i would‚Äôve known that money comes and goes, but love is always the ultimate goal. loving what you do, loving who loves you, and loving who you are is what matters most in the end.
